---
---

<section id="features" class="headline">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="section-eyebrow reveal">Why it's different</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Built for the way remote work actually happens.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub reveal">
      A session that survives, an agent that can act inside it, and your
      local dev ports reachable without thinking about it. Everything
      else — panes, files, chrome — sits on top of these three.
    </p>

    <div class="headline-grid">
      <article class="headline-card reveal">
        <div class="card-icon" style="color:var(--accent-text)">
          <svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <path d="M12 3v18M3 13h9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <span class="headline-tag">The core differentiator</span>
        <h3>Real tmux control mode, not a reimplementation</h3>
        <p>
          Smart Terminal runs <code class="mono">tmux -CC</code> on the
          remote and renders panes natively in the desktop UI. Your session
          lives inside tmux itself, so it keeps running through sleep,
          network drops, and app crashes. Reconnect and every pane,
          every scrollback line, every running process is exactly as you
          left it.
        </p>
        <ul class="headline-points">
          <li>Survives sleep, disconnects, and app restarts</li>
          <li>Native multi-pane rendering, not a dumb terminal in a box</li>
          <li>Scrollback and running processes untouched on reconnect</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="headline-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="card-icon" style="color:var(--agent)">
          <svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
            <path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3v1h1a3 3 0 0 1 3 3v6a3 3 0 0 1-3 3H8a3 3 0 0 1-3-3v-6a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h1V6a3 3 0 0 1 3-3Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <circle cx="9.5" cy="13.5" r="1" fill="currentColor"/>
            <circle cx="14.5" cy="13.5" r="1" fill="currentColor"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <span class="headline-tag" style="color:var(--agent)">The point of the persistence</span>
        <h3>An agent that lives in the terminal, not beside it</h3>
        <p>
          One input box, classified per line: plain shell or an instruction
          to the agent. Agent-run commands execute as real commands in real
          tmux scrollback — never a hidden side channel — so what the agent
          did is still there after you reconnect, exactly like your own
          history.
        </p>
        <ul class="headline-points">
          <li>Type shell or ask the agent — same box, no mode switch</li>
          <li>Agent commands land in tmux scrollback, not a separate log</li>
          <li>Structured command blocks give it (and you) something to read</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="headline-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="card-icon" style="color:var(--info)">
          <svg width="30" height="30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
            <rect x="2.5" y="8" width="7" height="8" rx="1.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <rect x="14.5" y="8" width="7" height="8" rx="1.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <path d="M9.5 10.4h5M9.5 13.6h5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M12.4 9.5 14 10.4l-1.6 0.9M14.6 12.7l1.6 0.9-1.6 0.9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <span class="headline-tag" style="color:var(--info)">Build remote, test local</span>
        <h3>Port forwarding that finds itself</h3>
        <p>
          Start a dev server on the remote and Smart Terminal spots it in
          the scrollback and offers to forward it — one click and it's live
          at <code class="mono">localhost</code>. Forwards persist across
          reconnects, so a tunnel you set up once just comes back.
        </p>
        <ul class="headline-points">
          <li>Auto-detects dev-server ports as they come up</li>
          <li>One click to forward back to a local port</li>
          <li>Persisted tunnels reconnect automatically, no re-setup</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .headline {
    background: var(--sidebar);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .headline-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .headline-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .headline-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
  .headline-card {
    background: linear-gradient(165deg, var(--surface) 0%, var(--bg) 100%);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 30px 26px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .headline-card::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: -1px;
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(213,154,74,0.5), transparent 40%);
    -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#000 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#000 0 0);
    -webkit-mask-composite: xor;
    mask-composite: exclude;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .card-icon {
    width: 56px;
    height: 56px;
    border-radius: 14px;
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .headline-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent-text);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .headline-card h3 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .headline-card p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 15.5px;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }
  .headline-card code {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }
  .headline-points {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .headline-points li {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    color: var(--text);
    padding-left: 24px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .headline-points li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 7px;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
</style>
